{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The Appcues iOS SDK includes support for a custom URL scheme that supports previewing Appcues experiences in-app prior to publishing and launching the Appcues debugger."}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"article","metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"AppcuesKit"}],"role":"article","title":"Configuring the Appcues URL Scheme","roleHeading":"Article"},"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"title":"Core Functionality","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/GettingStarted","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Identifying","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Tracking","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/AnchoredTooltips","doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues"]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/appcueskit\/urlschemeconfiguring"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/URLSchemeConfiguring","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Configuring the Appcues URL scheme involves adding a "},{"code":"CFBundleURLTypes","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" value and then directing the incoming URL to the Appcues iOS SDK.","type":"text"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"strongly"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" recommended that you configure the custom URL scheme. It allows non-developer users of your Appcues instance to test Appcues experiences in a real setting. It’s also valuable for future troubleshooting and support from Appcues via the debugger."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"style":"note","name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"type":"heading","text":"Register the Custom URL Scheme","anchor":"Register-the-Custom-URL-Scheme","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Update your ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Info.plist"},{"text":" to register the custom URL scheme. Replace ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"APPCUES_APPLICATION_ID"},{"text":" in the snippet below with your app’s Appcues Application ID. This value can be obtained from your ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/studio.appcues.com\/settings\/installation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For example, if your Appcues Application ID is "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"123-xyz"},{"type":"text","text":" your url scheme value would be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"appcues-123-xyz"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":null,"code":["<key>CFBundleURLTypes<\/key>","<array>","    <dict>","        <key>CFBundleTypeRole<\/key>","        <string>Editor<\/string>","        <key>CFBundleURLName<\/key>","        <string>$(PRODUCT_BUNDLE_IDENTIFIER)<\/string>","        <key>CFBundleURLSchemes<\/key>","        <array>","            <string>appcues-APPCUES_APPLICATION_ID<\/string>","        <\/array>","    <\/dict>","<\/array>"]},{"level":2,"anchor":"Handle-the-Custom-URL-Scheme","type":"heading","text":"Handle the Custom URL Scheme"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Custom URL’s should be handled with a call to "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/filterAndHandle(_:)","type":"reference"},{"text":" or ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.appcues.sdk\/documentation\/AppcuesKit\/Appcues\/didHandleURL(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". If the URL being opened is an Appcues URL, the URL will be handled."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your app uses a Scene delegate, add the following:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["func scene(_ scene: UIScene, willConnectTo session: UISceneSession, options connectionOptions: UIScene.ConnectionOptions) {","    \/\/ Handle Appcues deep links.","    let unhandledURLContexts = appcues.filterAndHandle(connectionOptions.urlContexts)","","    \/\/ Handle any links remaining in unhandledURLContexts.","}","","func scene(_ scene: UIScene, openURLContexts URLContexts: Set<UIOpenURLContext>) {","    \/\/ Handle Appcues deep links.","    let unhandledURLContexts = appcues.filterAndHandle(URLContexts)","","    \/\/ Handle any links remaining in unhandledURLContexts.","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If your app uses only an App delegate, add the following:","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["func application(_ application: UIApplication, open url: URL, options: [UIApplication.OpenURLOptionsKey : Any] = [:] ) -> Bool {","    \/\/ Handle Appcues deep links.","    guard !appcues.didHandleURL(url) else { return true }","","    \/\/ Handle a non-Appcues URL.","    return false","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A SwiftUI app can handle the custom URL scheme as part of the "},{"code":"onOpenURL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" modifier associated with the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Scene"},{"type":"text","text":" of your main "},{"code":"App","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["var body: some Scene {","    WindowGroup {","        MyApp()","        .onOpenURL { url in","            guard !appcues.didHandleURL(url) else { return }","        }","    }","}"]},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"Verifying-the-Custom-URL-Scheme","text":"Verifying the Custom URL Scheme"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The Appcues debugger allows you to easily validate that the Appcues deep link is properly configured.","type":"text"}],"type":"para